ENTRY            14868   20260331   20260617   20260617       1529
SUBENT        14868001   20260331   20260617   20260617       1529
BIB                 12         45
TITLE      Neutron capture cross sections of 74,76,78,80,82Se
AUTHOR     (H.D.Dearmon,K.S.Krane)
REFERENCE  (J,EPJ/A,55,135,2019)
           #doi:10.1140/epja/i2019-12821-4
INSTITUTE  (1USAORU)
FACILITY   (REAC,1USAORU) The Oregon State University TRIGA
           reactor.
INC-SPECT  Four different irradiation sites were used:
           --- a thermal column (TC - nominal thermal and
           epithermal neutron fluxes of respectively 8.0*10**10
           and 2.0*10**8 neutrons cm-2 s-1);
           --- In-core irradiation site, a Cd-lined site in the
           central core (CLICIT - 0 and 1.2*10**12 neutrons cm-2
           s-1);
           --- In-core irradiation site, a second in the outer
            core or G-ring (GRICIT - 4.3*10**12 and 3.9*10**12
           neutrons cm-2 s-1);
           --- A fast pneumatic transfer system ("rabbit" -
           8.3*10**12 and 3.3*10**11 neutrons cm-2 s-1).
DETECTOR   (HPGE) The gamma rays were observed with high-purity
           Ge detectors (nominal volume of 169 cm3, efficiency of
           35% compared with NaI at 1332 keV, resolution of 1.68
           keV at 1332 keV). Source-to-detector distances for the
           stronger sources were initially 20 cm, moving to 15
           cm as the source decayed. For the weaker sources the
           counting started at 15 cm and later moved to 10 cm.
SAMPLE     Se samples in the form of metal powder.
METHOD     (ACTIV) Irradiations for the cross section
           measurements lasted for 1 h in the GRICIT (GR) and
           CLICIT (CL) sites and 2 h in the thermal column (TC),
            and counting began about 2-3 h after the
           irradiations. Irradiations in the rabbit
            (R) were of duration 1-10 min, and counting began
           within 2-5 min for the short irradiations, in order
           to see the short-lived activities, and within 10-30
           minutes for the long-lived activities.
MONITOR    ((MONIT1)79-AU-197(N,G)79-AU-198,,SIG)
           ((MONIT2)79-AU-197(N,G)79-AU-198,,RI)
           ((MONIT3)27-CO-59(N,G)27-CO-60,,SIG)
           ((MONIT4)27-CO-59(N,G)27-CO-60,,RI)
MONIT-REF  ((MONIT1)V1002484,S.F.Mughabghab,B,NEUT.RES,,,2006)
           ((MONIT2)V1002486,S.F.Mughabghab,B,NEUT.RES,,,2006)
           ((MONIT3)V1001216,S.F.Mughabghab,B,NEUT.RES,,,2006)
           ((MONIT4)V1001217,S.F.Mughabghab,B,NEUT.RES,,,2006)
HISTORY    (20260331C)
ENDBIB              45
COMMON               8          6
MONIT1     MONIT1-ERR MONIT2     MONIT2-ERR MONIT3     MONIT3-ERR
MONIT4     MONIT4-ERR
